136-#### Finding 2 - High - Alternate approvals disappear from canonical case history
137-
138-The supported one-Director replacement path can approve through a frozen alternate, but
139-`serialize_case_detail` attaches actions only to the original `required_approvers_json`. The
140-approved response/readback can still show the excluded original Director as undecided and omit the
141-alternate entirely. The executable HTTP probe completed the case and then found zero alternate rows
142-in `required_approvers`. This breaks API §25.4 and 007D2's single history-aware projection claim.
143-`007E2` preserves immutable route provenance while projecting every effective replacement/action.
144-
145-#### Finding 3 - High - Ordinary list counts disclose cases to an unused committee alternate
146-
147-`ApprovalCase.save` populates `ApprovalCaseRequiredApprover` with every frozen committee candidate,
148-not only original/effective approvers. The SQL selector counts that table before the Python object-
149-scope check. On the lower rule, the unused second Director with `approvals.case.read` receives an
150-empty data array but `total_count: 1`; direct detail correctly returns 403. The focused HTTP probe
151-failed exactly `1 != 0`. This violates auth §§32.1/37.3 and the selector/count contract. `007E2`
152-backfills an exact approval-owned read projection and tests pre-pagination nondisclosure.
