230-#### Finding 1 - High - Approval-case reads overcorrect assignment scope and deny source readers
231-
232-007C2 correctly removes permission-implied global reads for arbitrary users and unassigned
233-Directors, but `can_read_approval_case` now allows only immutable required approvers. The source
234-role matrix says the Credit Manager can view the sanction package and Company Secretary/Auditor
235-have read access (auth §§14.1 and 26.3); object scope §19.1 explicitly names `audit_readonly` and
236-management/read-only scopes. The current catalogue does not grant these roles
237-`approvals.case.read`, and even a custom grant cannot pass the case predicate. `007C3` persists a
238-separate source-backed read scope, restores the named read-only roles, and keeps actions and
239-unassigned-Director access denied.
240-
241-#### Finding 2 - High - Return-for-clarification creates a permanent one-case dead end
242-
243-`record_action` closes the case as returned and restores reviewed statuses, but
244-`SanctionHandoffModule.submit_reviewed_appraisal` rejects every application that already has any
245-case. `ApprovalCase` also uses one-to-one application/appraisal links. A returned case therefore
246-cannot be corrected and submitted again. This conflicts with data-model's application-to-many-case
247-cardinality and codebase-design §13.1's invariant that material re-approval creates a new cycle;
248-the positive return test checks only the immediate status and misses the next public step. `007D3`
249-adds immutable numbered approval cycles and a fresh-review resubmission path.
